The paper deals with the problem of dexterous grasping using a robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves using active vision to guide the grasping process, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and machine learning algorithms (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques to improve the success rate of grasping, which falls under the category of optimization and learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of ensuring safety during the grasping process, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
